Reasoning: The paper focuses on the analysis of language and its impact on memorability, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to build a corpus of movie quotes and annotate them with memorability information, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of lexical distinctiveness and generalization in memorable quotes, which are concepts relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
